							<Properties>
								<ProtectedString name="Source"><![CDATA[--[[

----------------------------------
--//EasyLS Addon Documentation\\--
----------------------------------

addonLibrary is provided in the environment of any addon module.  It is a table of functions that are disposable to your addon code.

----------------------------------
----------------------------------
----------------------------------

<RBXScriptSignal> addonLibrary.StageChanged // can be connected to with :Connect(f), where function f recieves 2 parameters.  first, the main ELS numerical stage, second the director ELS numerical stage

<RBXScriptSignal> addonLibrary.keystroke(<keycode>) // .keystroke must be provided with a keycode, and will then return a signal.
                                                        this signal can be connected to with :Connect(f), where function f recieves no parameters.

<int,int> addonLibrary.getCurrentStage() // will return main and director ELS states, 0 being off and 1/2/3/4 being on respectivley

<instance> addonLibrary.DriveSeat // will return the drive seat of the car

<instance> addonLibrary.lightsParent // will return the lights parent set using EasyLS





]]]]></ProtectedString>
